column5: The Moose in I-Falls had really gone down hill. Stopped by several times during the the spring and summer. Service was slow and food quality was off. Pretty hard to mess up an egg, but they managed to do it. We stop in Orr now.

T Patton Cafe in Orr is the best bet for a good ol fashion stick to ya ribs kinda breakfast. Mcdonalds in the falls but that place is crazy busy on travel days and to me it seems poorly run with slow piss poor service. La Place de rendezvous on the Canada side is a good option as well.

Actually, it was Sandy's that closed due to retirement. will definitely miss her and her great food.. was the best in town.. tried a new place out on Third Street (M-11) next to Super One Foods called The Library... great breakfast and lunch.. and if you need a book to read take one.. they grind their own coffee beans.

With a return to Canada several times last summer, I was beyond disappointed with the options in the Falls. Shorelunch is long Gomes's, Patty's is closed due to retirement, Voyageurs was locked up tight both times through with no sign of life. What's left for a decent sit down breakfast with or even without decent parking?
Great news! All the places you mentioned that are closed are for sale. Bring your checkbook and staff and you can be a business owner in beautiful I-Falls. Chocolate Moose is your best option.
I like the Moose, their ham and cheese omelette and pancakes is pretty good.
And we better support the ones that are still around or they won't be around! Later, Jay

I’m glad I don’t need much of a breakfast Diet Coke is enough for me as we stopped at the Chocolate Moose and my friend’s breakfast was like $15. I’d rather put the pedal to the metal and get to the lake vs a sit down breakfast
We usually stop at the Village Inn in Virginia. Good food and plenty of parking.
I'm with you RichA. Cup of coffee, breakfast bar or banana, nature calls and let's roll to the launch.
If you are driving up 53 stop at T Pattenn Cafe in Orr, on the left side. Great old style breakfast
And the BIGGEST DONUTS IN TOWN !!!
Also the biggest bluegill statue,everything is big in Orr,just need to have big money when your there.
